  "texts": [
    "(7), the important point of the node sampling method is to design a suitable node scoring function so that the important nodes can be better retained.",
    "Gpool (Gao and Ji 2019b) scores nodes based on their scalar projection values on trainable projection vectors.",
    "Pool (Lee et al. 2019) transplants the self-attention mechanism into graph pooling and uses the self-attention mechanism to score nodes.",
    "ASAP (Ranjan et al. 2020) scores nodes using a variant of an attention network and a variant of a graph neural network.",
    "MVPool (Zhang et al. 2021b) scores nodes using the multi-view information and then incorporates a structure learning mechanism to construct new adjacency matrices for subgraphs to correct the topology of the subgraphs, which helps to maintain key information in the hierarchical representation of the graphs and improves the performance of tasks such as graph classification."
